<br>
Here is something I did in a minute or two to illustrate my point.<br>
<br>
Your drawing lacks perspective.<br>
<br>
the blue lines are the theoretical lines leading to the horizon.  As you see your characters shoulders (lined in red) do not line up with the perspective lines.  This makes your character seem posted on top of the background instead of in it.  As for the background you have no foothills or anything.  I added another range in black.  Mountains never just pop out of the ground, they have foothills, so make some in your picture.  Also obscure the characters feet, and subsequently the base of the mountains to make it easier on yourself.  This lets the perspective (which you should add!) do all the work<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
