<br>
The lower the horizon the lower the person viewing said picture is compared to the subject.<br>
<br>
If you are standing and looking at someone about the same height as you, their head will be near the horizon. If you were to sit down, their waist would be near the horizon. This works no matter how close or far they are from you.<br>
<br>
You pic would imply that I am lying on my belly, on the ground, looking up at the subject. This current subject is out of perspective with this arangement.<br>
<br>
Pretty simple huh?<br>
